WEBVTT

00:01.669 --> 00:04.706
TRINA: If you don't know
how to use a computer,
we will teach you here.

00:04.797 --> 00:07.630
Most jobs require at least
basic word processing skills.

00:07.717 --> 00:10.379
We try to get you up to
50 words per minute.

00:10.469 --> 00:14.303
We also have a course
in how to talk to someone
in an interview.

00:14.390 --> 00:16.881
Stuff like what
employers are looking for,

00:16.976 --> 00:18.557
how to turn
negatives into positives.

00:18.644 --> 00:20.760
We can also provide
clothes for the interview
if you need them.

00:20.855 --> 00:23.642
People donate
shoes and suits
all the time.

00:24.275 --> 00:27.517
What if I had
a history with drugs?

00:28.237 --> 00:30.023
That is nothing
to be ashamed of.

00:30.114 --> 00:31.900
Many of our clients
have struggled
with addiction,

00:31.991 --> 00:35.199
and if you want to get clean,
we'll help you do that.

00:35.286 --> 00:36.776
And what if
I have a kid?

00:37.872 --> 00:38.987
No one to help you?

00:39.081 --> 00:43.575
If I need someone to
watch her while I'm in
a class or on an interview,

00:44.253 --> 00:45.789
could you help with that?

00:45.880 --> 00:47.245
We do not provide
child care.

00:47.340 --> 00:49.706
Actually, it's something
that comes up often.

00:49.884 --> 00:51.875
lwould love to
be able to do it.

00:51.969 --> 00:53.925
| just don't
have the resources.

00:54.013 --> 00:56.550
But it's definitely
on the wish list.

00:57.433 --> 01:02.177
Okay.
Okay, uh, thank you.
I'll be back.

01:02.396 --> 01:03.647
(CELL PHONE RINGING)
l have to take this.

01:03.731 --> 01:05.972
Yes, please come back.
We'll get you started.

01:06.317 --> 01:09.229
It was nice to
meet you, Benjamin.

01:09.320 --> 01:10.901
Hey, Oscar.

01:11.781 --> 01:14.318
Ugh! That is too bad.

01:14.408 --> 01:16.364
Did they tell you why?

01:23.668 --> 01:24.828
Yeah.

01:26.170 --> 01:27.205
Mmm-hmm.

01:27.296 --> 01:30.834
Well, look, you know what?
Sometimes you just
don't get the job.

01:30.967 --> 01:33.504
Oscar, I've got to
call you back.

01:35.263 --> 01:36.343
Uh...

01:37.932 --> 01:39.172
Uh, uh...

01:43.354 --> 01:46.096
Benjamin!
Benjamin, wait.

01:51.362 --> 01:53.023
Oh, my God.

02:03.124 --> 02:05.490
Somebody call
an ambulance!

02:19.682 --> 02:20.762
(BUZZING)

02:20.850 --> 02:21.885
(CLICKING)

02:28.065 --> 02:29.271
(BUZZING)

03:08.064 --> 03:10.601
Why am I watching
you cut your hair?

03:10.733 --> 03:14.021
If I do it at home,
I'm the one who
has to clean it up.

03:14.111 --> 03:18.275
l was referring less
to where it's happening
and more to why.

03:18.366 --> 03:20.277
New life, new look.

03:21.952 --> 03:24.944
Does that mean you
like your new life?

03:25.081 --> 03:27.037
If you're asking
if yourjob is safe,

03:27.124 --> 03:30.116
that depends on
what you have to say about
the file you're holding.

03:30.252 --> 03:32.629
It doesn't seem
like much of a case.

03:32.713 --> 03:34.544
Although,
I'm sure I'm wrong.

03:34.632 --> 03:36.623
You are.
Tell me why.

03:36.759 --> 03:39.216
Guy collapsed after
being on his feet
for hours

03:39.303 --> 03:42.795
on a hot day
without breakfast,
so that's really weird.

03:42.890 --> 03:47.475
ER found nothing wrong,
then I decided
I should test his wallet.

03:47.603 --> 03:49.639
He's rich? That's why
we're taking the case?

03:49.730 --> 03:51.015
No, we're taking
the case because

03:51.107 --> 03:53.143
no one knows
what's wrong with him.

03:53.234 --> 03:54.815
And he's rich.

03:57.988 --> 03:59.489
Dr. Adams.

04:00.157 --> 04:01.567
Give her the file.

04:01.659 --> 04:03.240
This is my only copy.

04:04.620 --> 04:07.327
My MO depends upon
the use of a team.

04:07.415 --> 04:10.578
Definitionally,
that involves more
than one person,

04:10.668 --> 04:11.999
so I really have
no choice.

04:12.086 --> 04:14.168
Give her the file.
You can't afford a team.

04:14.505 --> 04:16.086
Adams is free.

04:16.173 --> 04:19.006
And I'm referring
both to her availability
and her price tag.

04:20.511 --> 04:23.628
New girl meet newer girl,
and vice versa.

04:24.765 --> 04:26.266
You said we were
meeting for coffee.

04:26.350 --> 04:28.716
Well, when someone
asks if you want coffee,

04:28.811 --> 04:31.018
they obviously
don't just mean coffee.

04:31.439 --> 04:34.931
Wait. Did you think
I was referring to sex?

04:35.025 --> 04:36.765
Would you
shut the blinds
on your way out?

04:36.861 --> 04:38.852
I thought you were
referring to talking.

04:38.988 --> 04:40.774
Talking about medicine.

04:40.865 --> 04:43.607
Specifically,
as it refers to the guy
whose name is on the file

04:43.701 --> 04:45.692
she still hasn't
handed you.

04:45.828 --> 04:49.696
I'm not working, House.
I'm in the process of
looking for a paying job.

04:49.790 --> 04:52.281
And in the meantime,
there's no way
a do-gooder like you

04:52.376 --> 04:54.116
isn't volunteering
all over town,

04:54.211 --> 04:56.372
ladling kittens,
spaying soup.

04:56.505 --> 04:58.712
There's a free clinic
in Trenton.

04:59.550 --> 05:01.415
Well, think of this
as today's free clinic.

05:01.510 --> 05:03.375
Only with fewer
bums with herpes.

05:03.471 --> 05:05.883
I don't think
we actually have
much of a case.

05:06.015 --> 05:08.347
I think it's
just dehydration.

05:10.060 --> 05:11.596
What happened
the last time
another doctor

05:11.687 --> 05:13.143
told you l was
wrong about a case?

05:13.230 --> 05:14.686
I lost my job.

05:15.399 --> 05:16.730
But you saved a life.

05:20.362 --> 05:23.650
Is an ultrasound
really necessary?
I'm feeling much better now.

05:23.741 --> 05:25.732
A sudden collapse
at your age can indicate

05:25.826 --> 05:27.487
a deterioration in
the heart muscle,

05:28.037 --> 05:29.743
a pretty serious
condition.

05:29.830 --> 05:32.321
It could also
just be dehydration.

05:32.416 --> 05:34.702
Next time,
you could probably
drop the undercover act.

05:35.044 --> 05:36.033
(CHUCKLES)

05:36.128 --> 05:40.167
I walk in in a suit,
and they're gonna put
their best foot forward.

05:40.257 --> 05:42.213
Also I don't own a suit.

05:43.052 --> 05:45.589
You give away millions,
and you don't own a suit?

05:45.679 --> 05:47.180
I gave those away too.

05:47.932 --> 05:49.888
One day l was writing
a check to my landscaper,

05:49.975 --> 05:51.511
and it suddenly hit me,
(LAUGHS)

05:51.602 --> 05:55.766
$6,000 to take out plants
and put in different plants

05:55.898 --> 05:58.014
so I can look at them.

05:58.108 --> 06:00.269
Shouldn't I use that money
to do something important?

06:00.402 --> 06:03.690
And by money,
you mean
all your money.

06:03.781 --> 06:05.021
I started with
$10 million,

06:05.115 --> 06:09.609
and then I couldn't
think of a reason
not to give 20 or 40.

06:11.747 --> 06:13.703
I figure I can live
on $25,000 a year.

06:14.124 --> 06:18.709
One room apartment,
bus pass, thrift stores,
bare necessities.

06:18.796 --> 06:21.287
I still have
my software company.

06:21.423 --> 06:24.551
And when I make more,
I'll give that away too.

06:24.635 --> 06:26.466
He's nuts.
He's generous.

06:26.971 --> 06:29.462
There's a neurological
issue. He's getting
rid of everything.

06:29.598 --> 06:32.214
His echocardiogram
was negative
for cardiomyopathy.

06:32.309 --> 06:34.561
Head CT showed no signs
of stroke or hemorrhage.

06:34.645 --> 06:36.055
He has one pair of pants!

06:36.146 --> 06:37.886
Most people with
his kind of money

06:37.982 --> 06:40.894
are commissioning
oil paintings of
their Yorkshire terrier.

06:40.985 --> 06:44.227
Benjamin is
sacrificing his own comfort
to help others.

06:44.321 --> 06:47.563
That's 'cause helping others
is his Yorkie oil painting.

06:47.658 --> 06:49.899
That's good, not sick.

06:49.994 --> 06:51.734
That's naive and sick.

06:51.829 --> 06:53.990
You really want to
improve things, you
do it through policy.

06:54.123 --> 06:56.739
This guy
empties his pockets,
what really changes?

06:56.834 --> 06:59.917
That's right.
All those babies with AIDS,
they're just using us.

07:00.254 --> 07:02.836
My parents had
$800 between them
when they got here.

07:02.965 --> 07:05.672
They scraped and
borrowed so we could
go to good schools.

07:05.759 --> 07:09.092
