31:10.870 --> 31:14.283
where even she thinks
that she's crazy.

31:24.800 --> 31:29.214
One more favor,
and I promise I'll
leave you alone forever.

31:29.305 --> 31:30.795
Or I'm lying.

31:30.890 --> 31:33.802
Either way, it's more
interesting than whatever
you're doing now.

31:43.486 --> 31:44.646
Can I help you?

31:44.820 --> 31:45.980
I'm his wife.

31:47.573 --> 31:48.813
We're separated.

31:48.908 --> 31:52.901
I heard he was sick.
ljust wanted to see him.

31:55.664 --> 31:57.791
He's giving a kidney
to someone he's never met?

31:59.418 --> 32:00.658
He wants to, yeah.

32:03.005 --> 32:04.745
I know
he's talked about you.

32:04.840 --> 32:06.580
He's been alone
all this time.

32:06.675 --> 32:08.666
I'm sure it would
mean a lot to him
to see you.

32:10.805 --> 32:13.387
I wanted to spend
my life with him,

32:16.352 --> 32:20.812
but I need to feel
like he loves me
more than other people.

32:20.898 --> 32:22.729
Like he loves
our kids more.

32:25.653 --> 32:27.644
Maybe that's selfish.

32:33.911 --> 32:35.401
I should go.

32:46.257 --> 32:47.588
Was that my wife?

32:47.716 --> 32:49.092
I don't know.

32:50.386 --> 32:52.001
Are you the guy,
the kidney donor?

32:54.723 --> 32:58.716
There was a problem,
but I'm gonna try again.

33:00.563 --> 33:01.552
Um...

33:01.647 --> 33:03.638
To give it to
the same lady?

33:03.732 --> 33:04.892
She needs it.

33:06.068 --> 33:07.854
Okay. Never mind.

33:07.945 --> 33:09.060
Wait.

33:10.239 --> 33:11.729
What do you want?

33:12.741 --> 33:14.902
Uh, it's nothing.
It's just...

33:20.249 --> 33:24.333
Ihave
polycystic kidney disease,
and I need a transplant,

33:24.420 --> 33:25.910
and they say
I don't have much time.

33:26.046 --> 33:28.662
So when I heard
that you were willing,
| just...

33:28.757 --> 33:31.248
But I'm glad
it's going to someone.

33:34.680 --> 33:35.760
I'll give it to you.

33:39.935 --> 33:42.187
But you already
promised it
to someone else.

33:42.271 --> 33:44.262
I have another one.

33:44.398 --> 33:47.856
Saving one life is good,
saving two is better.

33:48.194 --> 33:50.355
You give away two kidneys,
and you die.

33:50.446 --> 33:53.108
I could live on
dialysis for years.

33:53.240 --> 33:55.105
Yes, and then you die.

33:55.201 --> 33:59.535
And then I could
donate my other organs,
heart, lungs.

34:00.956 --> 34:02.947
I could save four
or five more lives.

34:21.310 --> 34:23.892
Foreman's going to
need a diagnostician.

34:23.979 --> 34:26.641
This guy is crazy.

34:32.321 --> 34:35.484
Arrhythmia, muscle tremors,
and yes, mental changes.

34:35.616 --> 34:38.323
If his heart doesn't rupture,
he's liable to rip it out
and give it away.

34:38.827 --> 34:40.613
You know,
the down vibe in here is

34:40.704 --> 34:43.491
totally ruining my
Charlie’s Angels fantasy.

34:43.958 --> 34:45.243
(MACHINERY WHIRRING)

34:45.334 --> 34:47.666
And that haircut
isn't helping, either.

34:47.753 --> 34:50.745
Seems like Graves disease
or some other thyroid issue.

34:50.839 --> 34:53.501
Is she on the team now,
like, forever?

34:56.011 --> 34:59.344
His thyroid levels
were within normal range
when he was admitted.

35:00.140 --> 35:01.641
Could be Coxsackie B virus.

35:01.725 --> 35:03.010
No pericarditis.

35:03.102 --> 35:05.434
What about porphyria?
It's a little weird
without the rash,

35:05.521 --> 35:07.011
but it fits all of
his other symptoms.

35:07.356 --> 35:09.438
And if it's acute
intermittent porphyria,

35:09.525 --> 35:11.516
that would explain
why his symptoms
keep recurring.

35:12.695 --> 35:14.981
Unlikely,
but it's possible.
What else?

35:15.656 --> 35:17.271
(MACHINE CONTINUES WHIRRING)

35:17.366 --> 35:18.697
I said, "What else?"

35:22.037 --> 35:24.619
Oh, for crying out loud.

35:28.210 --> 35:29.416
(WHIRRING STOPS)

35:40.389 --> 35:43.381
There, that's better.
Now, what else?

35:49.815 --> 35:51.931
Well, if there's
nothing better
than possible,

35:52.026 --> 35:54.108
then possible gets
upgraded to probable.

35:54.611 --> 35:55.896
I'll start him
on hematin.

35:55.988 --> 35:57.273
No, I'll go.

36:04.705 --> 36:07.071
So what's the answer?

36:07.166 --> 36:10.750
Are you now on the team,
like, forever?

36:10.836 --> 36:12.576
I don't know.

36:12.671 --> 36:15.287
Because I was thinking
of ordering t-shirts.

36:15.382 --> 36:18.874
I don't know, House.
I mean,
what am I supposed to do?

36:19.386 --> 36:23.595
I trained to be a doctor.
I know how to take
someone's pain away,

36:23.682 --> 36:25.843
how to make
a stopped heart
beat again.

36:26.852 --> 36:30.595
We've brought
people's kids back,
their husbands.

36:32.524 --> 36:33.684
So guilt?

36:33.776 --> 36:37.985
Yes, you were right.
You're always right.
ljust...

36:39.406 --> 36:41.988
I have the skills
to help people.

36:42.076 --> 36:47.161
Is it okay for me to
walk away from that
because I wanna just have fun?

36:49.083 --> 36:50.163
Obviously not.

36:50.417 --> 36:51.657
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

37:01.845 --> 37:04.052
How's your patient?

37:04.723 --> 37:06.805
She died a few hours ago.

37:14.942 --> 37:16.773
Thirteen's back.

37:18.987 --> 37:20.978
No department,
no money,

37:21.073 --> 37:23.735
and somehow,
you manage to con her
into hanging around.

37:24.868 --> 37:26.404
I have a gift.

37:32.418 --> 37:33.498
What?

37:33.669 --> 37:34.829
It was a con.

37:35.754 --> 37:36.834
The patient was faking?

37:37.172 --> 37:38.833
No, lwas.

37:41.552 --> 37:46.421
I brought him in here
under false pretenses
just to get his money.

37:47.266 --> 37:49.473
I ordered
a bunch of random tests
to keep him here.

37:49.560 --> 37:54.054
One of them was a head CT
which uses iodine contrast.

37:54.148 --> 37:55.513
You think he's
allergic to iodine?

37:55.774 --> 37:57.310
No. Again.

37:57.401 --> 37:59.312
Just don't interrupt me.

37:59.403 --> 38:02.645
Thirteen was right.
This is a thyroid issue.

38:05.742 --> 38:07.733
He has Plummer's disease.

38:11.331 --> 38:16.075
He has a nodule
in his thyroid.
It produces excess hormone.

38:16.170 --> 38:19.879
Not enough to test abnormal,
just more than
his brain was used to.

38:19.965 --> 38:22.297
Just enough to make him
irrational/y generous,

38:22.384 --> 38:24.466
make him
vulnerable to overheating.

38:24.553 --> 38:26.418
WILSON:
Then you pumped his body
full of iodine

38:26.513 --> 38:28.094
and kicked him
into thyrotoxicosis.

38:28.182 --> 38:30.343
I said don’t interrupt.

38:30.434 --> 38:34.393
But yes, you’re right.
We take out the nodule.
He’ll be fine.

38:48.619 --> 38:50.985
Two days, one surgery.

38:52.372 --> 38:55.159
I now accept that
you are all better.

38:56.210 --> 38:57.199
Where's my money?

38:57.294 --> 38:58.579
You made me sick.

38:58.670 --> 39:03.664
You were already sick.
I just made you much,
much worse.

39:04.885 --> 39:06.921
Seriously, the money.

39:11.016 --> 39:12.552
You're not giving
it to me, are you?

39:13.393 --> 39:18.057
When you're facing death,
some things come into focus...

39:19.525 --> 39:20.514
My wife...

39:20.609 --> 39:22.600
You love your family.
You want them back.

39:24.279 --> 39:27.066
Your altruism was
always a symptom.

39:27.824 --> 39:29.951
No, it wasn't.
I'm still gonna...

39:30.035 --> 39:32.617
Give less?
How much less?

39:32.704 --> 39:33.910
Just enough to
spoil your kids?

39:33.997 --> 39:35.157
No.

39:35.249 --> 39:37.365
But they need it
more than people with TB

39:37.459 --> 39:39.495
or children in Indonesia
with no eyes?

39:39.920 --> 39:41.831
Diagnosticians
with hearts of gold?

39:41.922 --> 39:44.789
I don't want
to give you money
because you're an ass.

39:47.135 --> 39:48.511
I was an ass last week.

39:51.890 --> 39:56.008
I love my family.
I want to be with them.

39:58.021 --> 39:59.557
That doesn't make me
a bad person.

39:59.773 --> 40:00.853
No.

40:02.025 --> 40:03.401
It makes you
a healthy person.

40:14.621 --> 40:18.113
My mechanic called.
Said the work's
been paid for.

40:18.208 --> 40:20.164
You mentioned your
car was in the shop.

40:20.252 --> 40:22.709
That's $4,500.

40:23.547 --> 40:27.756
Smile and say thank you,
or I get you GPS.

40:31.179 --> 40:32.339
You win.

40:37.185 --> 40:38.220
Thank you.

40:48.530 --> 40:52.193
Your car's getting fixed.
You were right.
She went for it.

40:53.619 --> 40:55.280
Good work.

40:56.204 --> 40:59.788
Need a lift tomorrow?
Your car's still in the shop.

40:59.875 --> 41:01.831
I don't take charity.

41:01.918 --> 41:03.374
I'm just glad it's over.

41:05.922 --> 41:08.049
Nothing is ever over.

41:29.321 --> 41:30.731
HOUSE: Thirteen.

41:32.449 --> 41:33.985
Need a minute.

41:41.750 --> 41:42.830
You're fired.

41:43.669 --> 41:45.000
Now what?
House, I'm starving...

41:45.087 --> 41:46.418
I'm notjoking.

41:47.422 --> 41:49.003
You're fired.
Don't come in tomorrow.

41:49.091 --> 41:50.126
House”.

41:51.927 --> 41:54.043
I can work with people
who've got nowhere else
to go,

41:54.137 --> 41:55.673
people who've got
something to prove,

41:55.764 --> 41:57.595
people who just get off
on weird cases.

41:57.766 --> 42:00.883
Who I can't work with
is someone who's here

42:00.977 --> 42:02.763
so she doesn't
have to feel bad.

42:06.775 --> 42:08.356
You're trying to save me.

42:08.443 --> 42:11.935
Yes,
I think that little of you
and that much of me.

42:24.126 --> 42:25.286
Okay.

42:29.631 --> 42:30.996
Bye, House.
